reviews.review_text:
Not To Be Missed Can't believe I'm the first to drop a review on this one, but once again Mister Miller has done it again and offered up a true delight and gem.  This is it, where it shines and glimmers in all of its glory.  This little Winterland run is fantastic and as a centerpiece of the trifecta it's among favorites from all of '77.

Be Well People.

Seems to be all new boards But likely just continuous improvement of the baseline "best" recordings... Meaning... wait, what the hell do I mean?!!? 
There seems an abundance of new and improved additions to the archive over the last year or so that I might suggest either new improved recordings (sources) were discovered, or the team that strive for an asymptotic approach to perfection! (I had to make sure I was using the word correctly...still not sure, but close enough... asymptotic! HaHaHa) Perfection! maybe not, but darn close!
Sorry, but I went down the rabbit hole and found great amusement in my bs
